- Reference [`docs/prep/icons.md`](docs/prep/icons.md) for more options

### Text Formatting
- **Bold** for:
  - Key terms and concepts
  - UI element names (buttons, menus, etc.)
  - Important file names
  - Emphasis on critical information
- *Italics* for:
  - Time estimates
  - Subtle emphasis
  - Alternative phrasing
- `Inline code` for:
  - File names
  - Commands
  - Code snippets
  - Technical terms
  - Branch names, folder paths

### File References
- **Always** use relative hyperlinks: [`filename.ext`](relative/path/to/file.ext)
- Link to images: `![Alt Text](relative/path/to/image.png)`
- Link to external resources: `[Link Text](https://url.com)`

### Lists
- Use `- [ ]` for actionable steps that users can check off as completed (checkboxes)
- Use `-` for informational items, explanations, context, or non-actionable content
- Use numbered lists `1.` for sequential processes where order matters
- Add icons to list items when helpful
- **Important**: Only use checkboxes when referring to a specific task a user can check off as having done

### Images
- Include screenshots showing what students should see
- Use descriptive alt text
- Place images after relevant steps
- Use relative paths: `../images/filename.png` or `../../images/filename.png`

