## Writing Style (All Types)

### Tone
- **Concise**: Get to the point; avoid unnecessary words
- **Humble**: Don't assume expertise; explain clearly
- **Direct**: State facts directly; avoid phrases like "it is obvious" or "it is critical"
- **Patient**: Remember audience is learning Git, AI, APIs for the first time

### Clarity
- Explain acronyms on first use
- Break complex steps into smaller sub-steps
- Provide context for why steps are needed
- Use simple language; define jargon inline

### Examples to Avoid
```markdown
âŒ It is critical that you complete this step.
âŒ Obviously, you should select the main branch.
âŒ As you can see, this is important.
```

### Examples to Use
```markdown
âœ… Complete this step to configure your API endpoint.
âœ… Select the main branch from the dropdown menu.
âœ… This step ensures your app deploys correctly.
```

